            <head>Search</head>
            <p>Searching is the most powerful means of accessing the information in Hofmeister XIX,
                using one or more different fields, together where desired with a date range. Four
                types of search are available:</p>
            <list>
                <item>
                    <xref type="internal" from="search_basic">Basic search</xref>
                </item>
                <item>
                    <xref type="internal" from="search_advanced">Advanced search</xref>
                </item>
                <item>
                    <xref type="internal" from="search_free_text">Free text search</xref>
                </item>
                <item>
                    <xref type="internal" from="search_list">List search</xref>
                </item>
            </list>
           <p>The purpose of the first three is to locate individual bibliographical items. List
                search is for extracting information about the items, such as a listing of all
                composers published at a particular time and place.</p>
            <!-- <p>Searching is the most powerful means of accessing the information in Hofmeister XIX,
